   "source": [
    "# Citation Analysis: Journals Citing a Research Organization \n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook shows how to use the [Dimensions Analytics API](https://www.dimensions.ai/dimensions-apis/) to discover what academic journals are most frequenlty citing publications from authors affiliation to a selected research organization. These are the steps: \n",
    "\n",
    "* We start from a [GRID](https://grid.ac/) identifier (representing a research organization in Dimensions) \n",
    "* We then select all publications citing research where at least one author is/as affiliated to the GRID organization\n",
    "* Finally, we group this publications by source (journal) and analyse the findings \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",

   "source": [
    "## 2. Choose a Research Organization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab_type": "text",
    "id": "L6uIjSVnGRQV"
   },
   "source": [
    "For the purpose of this exercise, we will are going to use [grid.471244.0](https://grid.ac/institutes/grid.471244.0). Feel free though to change the parameters below as you want, eg by [choosing another GRID organization](https://grid.ac/institutes).\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "---<br /><a href=\"https://app.dimensions.ai/discover/publication?or_facet_research_org=grid.414299.3\">Preview grid.414299.3 Dimensions &#x29c9;</a>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.HTML object>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "GRIDID = \"grid.414299.3\" #@param {type:\"string\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "    \n",
    "#@markdown The start/end year of publications used to extract patents\n",
    "YEAR_START = 2000 #@param {type: \"slider\", min: 1950, max: 2020}\n",
    "YEAR_END = 2016 #@param {type: \"slider\", min: 1950, max: 2020}\n",
    "\n",
    "if YEAR_END < YEAR_START:\n",
    "  YEAR_END = YEAR_START\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# gen link to Dimensions\n",
    "#\n",
    "def dimensions_url(grids):\n",
    "    root = \"https://app.dimensions.ai/discover/publication?or_facet_research_org=\"\n",
    "    return root + \"&or_facet_research_org=\".join([x for x in grids])\n",
    "\n",
    "from IPython.core.display import display, HTML\n",
    "display(HTML('---<br /><a href=\"{}\">Preview {} Dimensions &#x29c9;</a>'.format(dimensions_url([GRIDID]), GRIDID)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab_type": "text",
    "id": "5UU0dcEVI5xq"
   },
   "source": [
    "## 3. Building a Publications Baseset\n",
    "\n",
    "First we extract all publications where at least one of the authors is affiliated to GRID_ORG. \n",
    "\n",
    "This will then let us query for citing publications using the `reference_ids` field (see the [Dimensions API data model](https://docs.dimensions.ai/dsl/data-model.html) for more details). "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab": {},
    "colab_type": "code",
    "id": "2zk4l3XZI5xr",
    "outputId": "d69e8ee5-a64a-4d81-8652-876e5cb1ea71"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Starting iteration with limit=1000 skip=0 ...\u001b[0m\n",
      "0-1000 / 2705 (1.21s)\u001b[0m\n",
      "1000-2000 / 2705 (0.88s)\u001b[0m\n",
      "2000-2705 / 2705 (0.68s)\u001b[0m\n",
      "===\n",
      "Records extracted: 2705\u001b[0m\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "===\n",
      "Saved:  extraction1/pubs_grid.414299.3.csv\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "publications = dsl.query_iterative(f\"\"\"\n",
    "search publications \n",
    "    where research_orgs.id = \"{GRIDID}\"\n",
    "    and year in [{YEAR_START}:{YEAR_END}]\n",
    "    return publications[id+title+doi+year]\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# save the data\n",
    "pubs_cited = publications.as_dataframe()\n",
    "save_as_csv(pubs_cited, f\"pubs_{GRIDID}\")"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   },
   "source": [
    "## 4. Extracting Publications Citing the Baseset\n",
    "\n",
    "In the next step we extract all publications citing the publications previously extracted. This query will return JSON data which can be further analyzed e.g. to count the unique number of journals they were published in.\n",
    "\n",
    "E.g.:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "'publications': [\n",
    "  {'journal': {'id': 'jour.1295784',\n",
    "    'title': 'IEEE Transactions on Cognitive and Developmental Systems'},\n",
    "   'publisher': 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE)',\n",
    "   'year': 2018,\n",
    "   'id': 'pub.1061542201',\n",
    "   'issn': ['2379-8920', '2379-8939']},\n",
    "  {'journal': {'id': 'jour.1043581', 'title': 'International Geology Review'},\n",
    "   'publisher': 'Taylor & Francis',\n",
    "   'year': 2018,\n",
    "   'id': 'pub.1087302818',\n",
    "   'issn': ['0020-6814', '1938-2839']}, etc..\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the query template we use. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab": {},
    "colab_type": "code",
    "id": "-sixps_gI5xt"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "query_template = \"\"\"search publications \n",
    "                    where journal is not empty \n",
    "                    and reference_ids in {}\n",
    "                    return publications[id+journal+issn+year+publisher]\"\"\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab_type": "text",
    "id": "bQJ1IgS-I5xu"
   },
   "source": [
    "Note the `{}` part which is where we will put lists of publication IDs (from the previous extraction) during each iteration. This is to ensure our query is never too long (<400 IDs is a good way to ensure we never get an API error)."
   ]

   "source": [
    "pubids = list(pubs_cited['id'])\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# loop through all source-publications IDs in chunks and query Dimensions \n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"===\\nExtracting publications data ...\")\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "BATCHSIZE = 200\n",
    "VERBOSE = False # set to True to see extraction logs\n",
    "\n",
    "for chunk in tqdm(list(chunks_of(pubids, BATCHSIZE))):\n",
    "    query = query_template.format(json.dumps(chunk))\n",
    "    data = dsl.query_iterative(query, verbose=VERBOSE)\n",
    "    results += data.publications\n",
    "    time.sleep(0.5)\n",
    "    \n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# put the citing pub data into a dataframe, remove duplicates and save\n",
    "\n",
    "pubs_citing = pd.DataFrame().from_dict(results)\n",
    "print(\"===\\nCiting Publications found: \", len(pubs_citing))\n",
    "pubs_citing.drop_duplicates(subset='id', inplace=True)\n",
    "print(\"Unique Citing Publications found: \", len(pubs_citing))\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# split up nested journal columns into two columns\n",
    "journals = pubs_citing['journal'].apply(pd.Series).rename(columns={\"id\": \"journal.id\", \"title\": \"journal.title\"})\n",
    "pubs_citing = pd.concat([pubs_citing.drop(['journal'], axis=1), journals], axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# save\n",
    "save_as_csv(pubs_citing, f\"pubs_citing_{GRIDID}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#\n",
    "# preview the data\n",
    "print(\"===\\nPreview:\")\n",
    "pubs_citing.head(10)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## 5. Journal Analysis\n",
    "Finally, we can analyze the citing publications by grouping them by source journal. This can be achieved easily thanks to pandas' Dataframe methods.  \n",
    "\n",
    "> [pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/) is a popular Python software library for data manipulation and analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "Collapsed": "false",
    "colab_type": "text",
    "id": "AmXbVyY3I5xx"
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Number of Unique journals"
   ]
